SIMPLE: sequent
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sequent
<hw>Se"quent</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>sequens</ets>, <ets>-entis</ets>, p. pr. of <ets>sequi</ets> to
follow. See <er>Sue</er> to follow.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Following;
succeeding; in continuance.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>What to this was <qex>sequent</qex>⟦br⟧
Thou knowest already.</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Following as an effect; consequent.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sequent</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Sequent
<hw>Se"quent</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A follower.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>That which follows as a result; a
sequence.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sequential</ent>⟦br⟧
